{{Quote|You've been holding the council meetings in the Tower of the Hand.|King [[Joffrey Baratheon]] to Lord [[Tywin Lannister]]|The Bear and the Maiden Fair (episode)}}

The '''Tower of the Hand''' is a location within the [[Red Keep]] in [[King's Landing]]. It serves as the residence of the [[Hand of the King]] and his household. Among other rooms, it contains a dining room, the Hand's study, the Hand's bed chamber and connecting corridors and stairways.

sections.History:
=== [[Season 1]] ===
During his short tenure as [[Hand of the King]], [[Eddard Stark]] takes residence in the tower alongside his daughters [[Sansa Stark|Sansa]] and [[Arya Stark|Arya]].

=== [[Season 2]] ===
[[Tyrion Lannister]] takes up residence in the tower when he assumes the role of Hand of the King. Secretly, he also installs his lover [[Shae]] with him,&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The North Remembers]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; until she's discovered by [[Varys]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Night Lands]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Tyrion also has dinner with [[Janos Slynt]] in the Tower before exiling him to the [[Night's Watch]]. [[Cersei]] visits Tyrion in his bed chamber to confront him about his treatment of Slynt.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Night Lands]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

=== [[Season 3]] ===

After assuming the mantle of Hand of the King, [[Tywin Lannister]] takes residence in the Tower. He also has [[small council]] meetings take place in the Tower instead of the small council chamber.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Valar Dohaeris]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Bear and the Maiden Fair (episode)]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

=== [[Season 4]] ===

Before fleeing the city, [[Tyrion Lannister]] sneaks into the Tower, where he strangles his former lover [[Shae]], and then kills his father [[Tywin]] with a crossbow while he is on the privy.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
